page.title: 19Cellardyke Sea Queen
page.content: On Saturday 6th July the Cellardyke Improvement Fund held its annual Sea Queen Festival in aid of charity. The procession started. The Guard of Honour (local Guides & Brownies) lined up in front of the throne on Cellardyke harbour to await the arrival of this year's Sea Queen Amanda Barnett, the retiring Sea Queen Elizabeth Watson and the Royal Attendants who entered the harbour on the fishing boat "Antares" to a great welcome from the large crowd. The King at Arms (Jamie Dumbreck) read the proclamation then the Crown Bearer (Michael Barnett) and the 2 Trumpeters (Colin Baird & Derek Dickson) carried out their duties. After the crowning the principals either mounted a float or a horse drawn carriage for the procession to Cellardyke church for tea.
